						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Biotechnology/Relevant-publications/Crop-Wild-Relative-newsletter-Issue-8" title="Crop Wild Relative newsletter, Issue 8 " alt="link">Crop Wild Relative newsletter, Issue 8 </a></h2>

	
					<p>The newsletter <i>Crop wild relative</i> was initiated by the EC-funded PGR Forum project and later adopted as the newsletter of the Crop Wild Relative Specialist Group (CWRSG) of the IUCN Species Survival Commission (SSC). Issue 8 is the first of three issues to be published in the context of the <a href="http://www.pgrsecure.bham.ac.uk/" target="_self">PGR Secure project</a> (full title: <i>Novel characterization of crop wild relative and landrace resources as a basis for improved crop breeding</i>). The project focuses on ensuring that the genetic diversity inherent in crop wild relative (CWR) and landrace (LR) populations and which is important for crop improvement – particularly to adapt crops to grow in our changing climate – is conserved and available for use by plant breeders. The April 2012</p>
							<p><span class="date">4/06/2012</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Biotechnology/Relevant-publications/Crop-Wild-Relative-newsletter-Issue-8">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
